riDW lZur \" data-testid=\"prism-caption\">\n<div class=\"HXPPJ barbu yKsXL IzgMt VcHIt uhSzI YGNMU cRAsZ xqMcl QtRul \"><span class=\"hsDdd OOSI GpQCA lZur VlFaz \" style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\" data-testid=\"prism-truncate\"><span class=\"gtOSm FbbUW tUtYa vOCwz EQwFq yCufu eEak Qmvg nyTIa SRXVc vzLa jgBfc WXDas CiUCW kqbG zrdEG txGfn ygKVe BbezD UOtxr CVfpq xijV soGRS XgdC sEIlf daWqJ \">Workers at the University of Arizona hand-load 19 tons of E6 glass into a rotating furnace that will cast the final mirror for the Giant Magellan Telescope. The glass is melted over a honeycombed mold, which will give the 27.5-footwide mirror a stiff, lightweight structure. Once cast, the mirror will be slowly cooled for three months, after which it will undergo an extensive grinding and polishing process that could last a year or more.<\/span><\/span><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"NYwzQ vUYNV glxIO ilAoG HPkGR \">\n<div>\n<figure class=\"kzIjN GNmeK pYrtp dSqFO \" data-testid=\"prism-figure\">\n<div class=\"Kiog gTIDq DtvAy ZcEtc IRwwZ \">\n<div class=\"lZur asrEW \">\n<figure class=\"kzIjN GNmeK pYrtp dSqFO \" data-testid=\"prism-figure\">\n<div class=\"GpQCA lZur \" data-testid=\"prism-ratio-frame\">\n<div class=\"FvQLF iLTd NqeUA UzzHi iWsMV \">\n<div class=\"lZur TmzDJ bmjsw \" data-testid=\"prism-copyright-wrapper\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><picture data-testid=\"prism-picture\"><source srcset=\"https:\/\/i.natgeofe.com\/n\/ab9bea4d-1af3-4646-a073-3a43f1c336b1\/MM9817_230910_02772.jpg?w=374&amp;h=274, https:\/\/i.natgeofe.com\/n\/ab9bea4d-1af3-4646-a073-3a43f1c336b1\/MM9817_230910_02772.jpg?w=748&amp;h=548 2x\" media=\"(max-width: 374px)\" \/><source srcset=\"https:\/\/i.natgeofe.com\/n\/ab9bea4d-1af3-4646-a073-3a43f1c336b1\/MM9817_230910_02772.jpg?w=413&amp;h=302, https:\/\/i.natgeofe.com\/n\/ab9bea4d-1af3-4646-a073-3a43f1c336b1\/MM9817_2